            "answer_text": "What I presume you mean here is do scientists ever question the knowledge we have gleaned from the world using the scientific method? If a scientist was to question 'science' he would be questioning the method with which the infomation was acquired. Maybe he didn't control all the variables and they can design a better experiment. As far as questioning the validity of our knowledge goes, the answer is yes. Scientists are highly motivated to question knowledge that we take for granted. The more fundamental the idea the scientist proved to be wrong, the bigger the boost to their career!  If you could prove evolution to be wrong your name would live in history forever! ",
